                <p><strong>What is the problem we want to address?</strong></p>
                <img src="~/Images/realInclusion.png" style="float:right" />
                <p>
                    We want to help people with disabilities to reach main
                    stream education and have employment opportunities.
                    Approximately 1% of the Karnataka population consist of
                    children with special needs. This aggregates to a
                    whopping 5 lakh children and out of this, the survey
                    indicates that only 1% of the children with special needs
                    go to school and complete secondary education. Rest 99%
                    of the children with special needs never attend school and
                    remain illiterate thus leading to increased dependency on
                    others for livelihood. Our aim is to ensure the remaining
                    99% children also get the basic training and become
                    ready to go to a mainstream school.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    <strong>
                        Do we have existing government schemes
                        to support such causes? How is SRP different?
                    </strong>
                </p>

